{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C8jjTKDvbohH1CXzw15aCy","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# 03 — Instrumentation: Locations & Types\n2\t\n3\tInstrument inventory, types, ranges/accuracies, and **measurement locations** from ANL-ART-47 §4.1–\n4\t§4.2. This section describes *where and how quantities are measured* — no measured values are included.\n5\t\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\t## 1. Data acquisition (§4.1)\n9\t- Control software LabVIEW 2012; all devices networked over TCP/IP (LUNA fiber system runs on a\n10\t  dedicated computer). DAQ boards at four points along the test section.\n11\t- National Instruments hardware (Table 11):\n12\t\n13\t| Qty | Model | Description |\n14\t|---|---|---|\n15\t| 4 | cDAQ-9188 | 8-slot cDAQ chassis |\n16\t| 26 | NI-9214 | 16-ch isothermal thermocouple input module |\n17\t| 2 | NI-9205 | 32-ch ±200 mV–±10 V, 16-bit analog input |\n18\t| 4 | WSN-3212 | 4-ch, 24-bit programmable thermocouple input node (wireless, chimney TCs) |\n19\t| 1 | NI-9265 | 4-ch, 16-bit, 0–20 mA analog output (chimney damper actuators) |\n20\t\n21\t---\n22\t\n23\t## 2. Instrumentation summary (§4.2, Table 12)\n24\t| Measurement | Instrument | # | Range | Accuracy |\n25\t|---|---|---|---|---|\n26\t| Power | Eurotherm EPower | 40 | 0–12 kW | ±1% |\n27\t| Heat flux | iTi Inc. model BHT | 16 | 0–300 kW/m² | ±5% |\n28\t| Temp — gas space (Type-K) | — | 34 | 0–1,250 °C | ±1.1 °C or 0.4% |\n29\t| Temp — riser wall (Type-K) | — | 32 | 0–1,250 °C | ±1.1 °C or 0.4% |\n30\t| Temp — heated plate (Type-K) | — | 125 | 0–1,250 °C | ±1.1 °C or 0.4% |\n31\t| Temp — insulation wall (Type-K) | — | 193 | 0–1,250 °C | ±2.2 °C or 1.1% |\n32\t| Temp — ceramic heater (Type-K) | — | 40 | 0–1,250 °C | ±2.2 °C or 1.1% |\n33\t| Mass flow rate | Sierra 640S | 1 | 0–1 kg/s | ±1% + 0.3 kg/min |\n34\t| Chimney velocity | Dwyer 160F | 2 | ±0–45 m/s | ±8.3% |\n35\t| Riser ΔP | Dwyer 668-11 | 8 | ±64 Pa | ±1% |\n36\t| Chimney ΔP | Dwyer 607-0B | 2 | ±24 Pa | ±0.5% |\n37\t| Humidity | Dwyer RHP | 1 | 3–95 %RH | ±2% |\n38\t| Wind speed | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 1–80 m/s | ±5% |\n39\t| Wind direction | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 0–360° | ±3° |\n40\t| Outdoor humidity | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 1–100 %RH | ±3% |\n41\t| Outdoor temperature | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | −40 to +65 °C | ±0.5 °C |\n42\t| Rainfall | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 0–6553 mm | ±4% |\n43\t| Barometric pressure | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 410–820 mmHg | ±0.8 mmHg |\n44\t\n45\tTotal thermocouples: **424**, Type-K. General accuracy ±2.2 °C or 0.75%; special-limits-of-error\n46\t(SLE) sensors (riser inlet/outlet gas, heated-plate surface) ±1.1 °C or 0.4%.\n47\t\n48\t---\n49\t\n50\t## 3. Wall thermocouples (§4.2.1)\n51\t- Majority on heated plates and surrounding insulated panels; flush-mounted for surface temperature.\n52\t- Heated-plate TC mounting (Fig. 30): wires passed through the 1″ plate via a 5/32″ dia hole\n53\t  countersunk 90° to a 1/4″ opening; bonded with high-temp cement; wires not joined at junction\n54\t  (circuit completed through the steel plate → detachment detectable as open circuit).\n55\t\n56\t## 4. Heat-flux sensors (§4.2.2, Table 13)\n57\t- 16 sensors (up to 19 IDs listed), iTi Inc. model BHT with polyimide HFT; NIST-calibrated to 5%,\n58\t  rated to 300 °C. Two surface types: matte-black (ε ≈ 1.0, total flux) and reflective golden\n59\t  (ε ≪ 1.0, convective-only) — the pair separates convective vs radiative components.\n60\t- **Locations** (Table 13; \"mm\" = elevation along riser; the Kradiative column is a per-sensor\n61\t  calibration sensitivity in W/m²·mV, not a test measurement):\n62\t\n63\t| # | Sensor ID | Kradiative | Finish | Location |\n64\t|---|---|---|---|---|\n65\t|1|950|20.20|matte|Hot side, duct 1, 100 mm|\n66\t|2|951|65.72|reflective|Hot side, duct 1, 100 mm|\n67\t|3|948|21.59|matte|Hot side, duct 1, 3500 mm|\n68\t|4|1358|15.92|matte|Hot side, duct 1, 7000 mm|\n69\t|5|933|21.73|matte|Cold side, duct 1, 7000 mm|\n70\t|6|939|18.15|matte|Cold side, duct 1, 7000 mm|\n71\t|7|1360|15.12|matte|Hot side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n72\t|8|1362|41.07|reflective|Hot side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n73\t|9|946|19.11|matte|Hot side, duct 7, 7000 mm|\n74\t|10|942|18.55|matte|Cold side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n75\t|11|935|52.97|reflective|Cold side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n76\t|12|940|24.68|matte|Hot side, duct 11, 3500 mm|\n77\t|13|941|22.07|matte|Hot side, duct 11, 7000 mm|\n78\t|14|936|62.43|reflective|Hot side, duct 11, 7000 mm|\n79\t|15|932|19.77|matte|Cold side, duct 11, 350 mm|\n80\t|16|938|22.88|matte|Cold side, duct 11, 700 mm|\n81\t|17|1355|15.54|matte|South side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n82\t|18|1356|15.24|matte|North side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n83\t|19|1359|44.62|reflective|Hot side, duct 1, 7000 mm|\n84\t\n85\t## 5. Meteorological (§4.2.3, Table 14)\n86\t- Davis VantageVue weather station on Bldg. 308 roof, wireless to control room. Measures barometric\n87\t  pressure, temperature, humidity, wind speed & direction, rainfall. Polls 1 record/min.\n88\t- Resolutions/ranges: Baro 0.1 mmHg / 410–820 mmHg; Humidity 0.01 / 1–100%; Rainfall 0.2 mm /\n89\t  0–6553 mm; Temperature 0.1 °C / −40 to 60 °C; Wind direction 1° / 0–360°; Wind speed 0.1 m/s /\n90\t  1–80 m/s; Wind run 0.01 km.\n91\t\n92\t## 6. Differential pressure (§4.2.4, Table 15)\n93\t- Riser ΔP: **Dwyer 668-11**, installed across 8 of the 12 risers (ducts 3, 5, 8, 10 omitted),\n94\t  bidirectional span ±0.25″ w.c. (±64 Pa). TCs co-located at each tap for gravitational-term\n95\t  separation.\n96\t- Chimney ΔP: **Dwyer 607-0B**, across both chimney networks, bidirectional ±0.10″ w.c. (±24 Pa).\n97\t\n98\t## 7. Inlet flow & humidity (§4.2.5, Tables 16–17)\n99\t- **Sierra 640S** thermal mass flow meter located in the inlet downcomer, 24″ past the flow\n100\t  conditioner, extending to the duct centerline.\n101\t- **Dwyer RHP-2O11** humidity probe positioned 24″ above and on the centerline of the 24″ inlet\n102\t  entrance (inlet plenum).\n103\t\n104\t## 8. Hot-wire probes (§4.2.6)\n105\t- Dantec constant-temperature anemometer (CTA) probes: 3-mm OD body, 10-µm tungsten wire; 0.2–500 m/s,\n106\t  max process temp 300 °C; operate at constant wire temp 242 °C; sampled at 50 kHz; co-located TC for\n107\t  temperature correction. Used at inlet and riser-outlet conditions.\n108\t\n109\t## 9. Pitot tubes (§4.2.7)\n110\t- Two Dwyer model **160F** pitot tubes along the chimney ductwork (replaced chimney ΔP for isolating\n111\t  friction). 304 SS, K-factor Kp = 0.81, ±2% FS over 0–45 m/s. Treated as *relative* chimney-to-\n112\t  chimney velocities (installation < 10 L/D). Velocity relation: V = Kp·√(2ΔP/ρ).\n113\t\n114\t## 10. Gas temperature (§4.2.8)\n115\t- Within each riser: Type-K TCs (ARI Industries T-22N-12BK8A-96(MOD)) extending to the lengthwise\n116\t  (10″) duct centerline. **Inlet TC** 0.75″ from the bottom lip on the cold side; **outlet TC** 4.0″\n117\t  below the top lip on the hot side.\n118\t- Outlet plenum: five instrumented insulation panels. The four vertical sides (N,S,E,W) each have\n119\t  6 embedded interior wall TCs; the top ceiling panel adds identical wall TCs plus **7 thermocouple\n120\t  rakes** for bulk gas temperature. Each rake carries 6 junctions, extending ~170 cm along the\n121\t  188-cm plenum height.\n122\t\n123\t## 11. Luna fiber-optic distributed temperature (§4.2.9, Tables 18–19)\n124\t- Luna **ODiSi A-10** distributed Rayleigh-scatter fiber sensing. 155-µm polyimide-coated single-mode\n125\t  telecom fiber (Specialty Photonics CL POLY 1310). Max sensing length 10 m; ~10-mm spacing at 1 Hz\n126\t  (≈ 9,750 pts/s per 7.5-m fiber); temp range −50 to 300 °C; single-scan repeatability ±0.2 °C.\n127\t- Installed in 1/16″ OD × 0.030″ ID stainless capillaries (free expansion; secured only at head).\n128\t- **Locations:** two riser ducts, **#6 and #9** — 6 fibers on the outside wall and 5 within the gas\n129\t  space. Measurement is a temperature *difference* from baseline → 16 NIST-calibrated Type-K wall TCs\n130\t  positioned along the duct walls for baseline calibration.\n131\t- Special-handling requirements (Table 19): strain-free mounting, reference-fiber calibration,\n132\t  humidity correction (~0.15 °C shift per %RH), and post-install annealing.\n133\t\n134\t---\n135\tReference note: heater power controllers (40× Eurotherm EPower) and the heater control architecture\n136\tare described in **04_conditions.md** (§4.3), since they define the controlled power input.\n137\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d866f6b4-d360-4fea-b150-307ad8af7258","uuid":"7192ca5b-dd6e-4e0b-a70a-9766ddc79282","timestamp":"2026-07-02T09:47:31.455Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/bench/curated_v2/inputs/03_instrumentation.md","content":"# 03 — Instrumentation: Locations & Types\n\nInstrument inventory, types, ranges/accuracies, and **measurement locations** from ANL-ART-47 §4.1–\n§4.2. This section describes *where and how quantities are measured* — no measured values are included.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Data acquisition (§4.1)\n- Control software LabVIEW 2012; all devices networked over TCP/IP (LUNA fiber system runs on a\n  dedicated computer). DAQ boards at four points along the test section.\n- National Instruments hardware (Table 11):\n\n| Qty | Model | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| 4 | cDAQ-9188 | 8-slot cDAQ chassis |\n| 26 | NI-9214 | 16-ch isothermal thermocouple input module |\n| 2 | NI-9205 | 32-ch ±200 mV–±10 V, 16-bit analog input |\n| 4 | WSN-3212 | 4-ch, 24-bit programmable thermocouple input node (wireless, chimney TCs) |\n| 1 | NI-9265 | 4-ch, 16-bit, 0–20 mA analog output (chimney damper actuators) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Instrumentation summary (§4.2, Table 12)\n| Measurement | Instrument | # | Range | Accuracy |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Power | Eurotherm EPower | 40 | 0–12 kW | ±1% |\n| Heat flux | iTi Inc. model BHT | 16 | 0–300 kW/m² | ±5% |\n| Temp — gas space (Type-K) | — | 34 | 0–1,250 °C | ±1.1 °C or 0.4% |\n| Temp — riser wall (Type-K) | — | 32 | 0–1,250 °C | ±1.1 °C or 0.4% |\n| Temp — heated plate (Type-K) | — | 125 | 0–1,250 °C | ±1.1 °C or 0.4% |\n| Temp — insulation wall (Type-K) | — | 193 | 0–1,250 °C | ±2.2 °C or 1.1% |\n| Temp — ceramic heater (Type-K) | — | 40 | 0–1,250 °C | ±2.2 °C or 1.1% |\n| Mass flow rate | Sierra 640S | 1 | 0–1 kg/s | ±1% + 0.3 kg/min |\n| Chimney velocity | Dwyer 160F | 2 | ±0–45 m/s | ±8.3% |\n| Riser ΔP | Dwyer 668-11 | 8 | ±64 Pa | ±1% |\n| Chimney ΔP | Dwyer 607-0B | 2 | ±24 Pa | ±0.5% |\n| Humidity | Dwyer RHP | 1 | 3–95 %RH | ±2% |\n| Wind speed | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 1–80 m/s | ±5% |\n| Wind direction | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 0–360° | ±3° |\n| Outdoor humidity | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 1–100 %RH | ±3% |\n| Outdoor temperature | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | −40 to +65 °C | ±0.5 °C |\n| Rainfall | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 0–6553 mm | ±4% |\n| Barometric pressure | Davis Vantage Vue | 1 | 410–820 mmHg | ±0.8 mmHg |\n\nTotal thermocouples: **424**, Type-K. General accuracy ±2.2 °C or 0.75%; special-limits-of-error\n(SLE) sensors (riser inlet/outlet gas, heated-plate surface) ±1.1 °C or 0.4%.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Wall thermocouples (§4.2.1)\n- Majority on heated plates and surrounding insulated panels; flush-mounted for surface temperature.\n- Heated-plate TC mounting (Fig. 30): wires passed through the 1″ plate via a 5/32″ dia hole\n  countersunk 90° to a 1/4″ opening; bonded with high-temp cement; wires not joined at junction\n  (circuit completed through the steel plate → detachment detectable as open circuit).\n\n## 4. Heat-flux sensors (§4.2.2, Table 13)\n- 16 sensors (up to 19 IDs listed), iTi Inc. model BHT with polyimide HFT; NIST-calibrated to 5%,\n  rated to 300 °C. Two surface types: matte-black (ε ≈ 1.0, total flux) and reflective golden\n  (ε ≪ 1.0, convective-only) — the pair separates convective vs radiative components.\n- **Locations** (Table 13; \"mm\" = elevation along riser; the Kradiative column is a per-sensor\n  calibration sensitivity in W/m²·mV, not a test measurement):\n\n| # | Sensor ID | Kradiative | Finish | Location |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n|1|950|20.20|matte|Hot side, duct 1, 100 mm|\n|2|951|65.72|reflective|Hot side, duct 1, 100 mm|\n|3|948|21.59|matte|Hot side, duct 1, 3500 mm|\n|4|1358|15.92|matte|Hot side, duct 1, 7000 mm|\n|5|933|21.73|matte|Cold side, duct 1, 7000 mm|\n|6|939|18.15|matte|Cold side, duct 1, 7000 mm|\n|7|1360|15.12|matte|Hot side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n|8|1362|41.07|reflective|Hot side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n|9|946|19.11|matte|Hot side, duct 7, 7000 mm|\n|10|942|18.55|matte|Cold side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n|11|935|52.97|reflective|Cold side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n|12|940|24.68|matte|Hot side, duct 11, 3500 mm|\n|13|941|22.07|matte|Hot side, duct 11, 7000 mm|\n|14|936|62.43|reflective|Hot side, duct 11, 7000 mm|\n|15|932|19.77|matte|Cold side, duct 11, 350 mm|\n|16|938|22.88|matte|Cold side, duct 11, 700 mm|\n|17|1355|15.54|matte|South side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n|18|1356|15.24|matte|North side, duct 7, 3500 mm|\n|19|1359|44.62|reflective|Hot side, duct 1, 7000 mm|\n\n## 5. Meteorological (§4.2.3, Table 14)\n- Davis VantageVue weather station on Bldg. 308 roof, wireless to control room. Measures barometric\n  pressure, temperature, humidity, wind speed & direction, rainfall. Polls 1 record/min.\n- Resolutions/ranges: Baro 0.1 mmHg / 410–820 mmHg; Humidity 0.01 / 1–100%; Rainfall 0.2 mm /\n  0–6553 mm; Temperature 0.1 °C / −40 to 60 °C; Wind direction 1° / 0–360°; Wind speed 0.1 m/s /\n  1–80 m/s; Wind run 0.01 km.\n\n## 6. Differential pressure (§4.2.4, Table 15)\n- Riser ΔP: **Dwyer 668-11**, installed across 8 of the 12 risers (ducts 3, 5, 8, 10 omitted),\n  bidirectional span ±0.25″ w.c. (±64 Pa). TCs co-located at each tap for gravitational-term\n  separation.\n- Chimney ΔP: **Dwyer 607-0B**, across both chimney networks, bidirectional ±0.10″ w.c. (±24 Pa).\n\n## 7. Inlet flow & humidity (§4.2.5, Tables 16–17)\n- **Sierra 640S** thermal mass flow meter located in the inlet downcomer, 24″ past the flow\n  conditioner, extending to the duct centerline.\n- **Dwyer RHP-2O11** humidity probe positioned 24″ above and on the centerline of the 24″ inlet\n  entrance (inlet plenum).\n\n## 8. Hot-wire probes (§4.2.6)\n- Dantec constant-temperature anemometer (CTA) probes: 3-mm OD body, 10-µm tungsten wire; 0.2–500 m/s,\n  max process temp 300 °C; operate at constant wire temp 242 °C; sampled at 50 kHz; co-located TC for\n  temperature correction. Used at inlet and riser-outlet conditions.\n\n## 9. Pitot tubes (§4.2.7)\n- Two Dwyer model **160F** pitot tubes along the chimney ductwork (replaced chimney ΔP for isolating\n  friction). 304 SS, K-factor Kp = 0.81, ±2% FS over 0–45 m/s. Treated as *relative* chimney-to-\n  chimney velocities (installation < 10 L/D). Velocity relation: V = Kp·√(2ΔP/ρ).\n\n## 10. Gas temperature (§4.2.8)\n- Within each riser: Type-K TCs (ARI Industries T-22N-12BK8A-96(MOD)) extending to the lengthwise\n  (10″) duct centerline. **Inlet TC** 0.75″ from the bottom lip on the cold side; **outlet TC** 4.0″\n  below the top lip on the hot side.\n- Outlet plenum: five instrumented insulation panels. The four vertical sides (N,S,E,W) each have\n  6 embedded interior wall TCs; the top ceiling panel adds identical wall TCs plus **7 thermocouple\n  rakes** for bulk gas temperature. Each rake carries 6 junctions, extending ~170 cm along the\n  188-cm plenum height.\n\n## 11. Luna fiber-optic distributed temperature (§4.2.9, Tables 18–19)\n- Luna **ODiSi A-10** distributed Rayleigh-scatter fiber sensing. 155-µm polyimide-coated single-mode\n  telecom fiber (Specialty Photonics CL POLY 1310). Max sensing length 10 m; ~10-mm spacing at 1 Hz\n  (≈ 9,750 pts/s per 7.5-m fiber); temp range −50 to 300 °C; single-scan repeatability ±0.2 °C.\n- Installed in 1/16″ OD × 0.030″ ID stainless capillaries (free expansion; secured only at head).\n- **Locations:** two riser ducts, **#6 and #9** — 6 fibers on the outside wall and 5 within the gas\n  space. Measurement is a temperature *difference* from baseline → 16 NIST-calibrated Type-K wall TCs\n  positioned along the duct walls for baseline calibration.\n- Special-handling requirements (Table 19): strain-free mounting, reference-fiber calibration,\n  humidity correction (~0.15 °C shift per %RH), and post-install annealing.\n\n---\nReference note: heater power controllers (40× Eurotherm EPower) and the heater control architecture\nare described in **04_conditions.md** (§4.3), since they define the controlled power input.\n","numLines":137,"startLine":1,"totalLines":137}}}
